<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-24T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-24T20:00:00-05:00" n="124" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d124">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/148<hi rend="superscript">1/12</hi>: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Long</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-24T20:00:00-05:00">May 24, 1940—8
                                            p.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 25—12:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>68. The Provisional President<note n="44" xml:id="d124fn1">Andrés
                                        F. Córdova.</note> approves plan outlined in Department’s
                                    No. 46, May 23, noon,<note n="45" xml:id="d124fn2">See footnote
                                        29, <ref target="#pg_16">p. 16</ref>.</note> and will be
                                    pleased to receive emissaries. Secrecy emphasized as per
                                    instructions.</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>